Business Brief -- Lewis Galoob Toys Inc.:
   Earnings of Just $121,000
   Posted in Fourth Quarter
Game Genie, which plugs into Nintendo game cartridges and
enhances the video characters, accounted for about half of
the quarter's sales. The net loss in the period included
extraordinary severance-related payments of $971,000.
   For the full year, Galoob had a net loss of $7.5 million,
or $1.14 a share, narrower than the net loss of $29.2
million, or $3.48 a share, in 1990. Sales rose 19% to $150.6
million from $126.9 million.